Four capsules containing
a known amount of highly enriched U-233 were
irradiated in the MTR and subsequently analyzed for
total and isotopic uranium concentration. Based on
these data, the effective alpha values (at a Cd ratio
for Co=15) and the computed 2200 m/sec values were
deduced.
Four standard burnup capsule
CIPP-6-2-4, contained 58.8+-0.2 mg of enriched U3O8,

CIPP-6-4-3, contained 126.0 mg of enriched U3O8,
CIPP-6-5-1, contained 144.4+0.2 mg of enriched U3O8.

Westcott quoted uncertainties for the various g values.
Two capsules containing a known
amount of highly enriched U-235 were irradiated in the
MTR and subsequently analyzed for total and isotopic
uranium concentration. Based on these data, the
effective alpha values (at a Cd ratio for Co=15) and
the computed 2200 m/sec values were deduced.

The capsule containing a weighed
quantity of highly enriched U-233 were irradiated to
~12 atom percent fission, were dissolved and
analyzed for the number of atoms of each uranium
isotope and for the number of atoms of the various
stable and long-lived fission product nuclides. The
absolute fission yield values determined on the
second U-233 capsule are given below.
Standard burnup capsule CIPP-6-4-3, contained
126.0 mg of enriched U3O8.

The capsule containing a weighed
quantity of highly enriched U-235 were irradiated to
~12 atom percent fission, were dissolved and analyzed
for the number of atoms of each uranium isotope and
for the number of atoms of the various stable and
long-lived fission product nuclides. The weighted
average of the absolute U-235 fission yields
determined on the first and second U-235 capsules.
Samples 115.2+-0.1 and 81.94+-0.10 mg of U3O8.
